## Emotional Signal Types & Risk Mapping

### Core Categories

| Type | Example Outputs | Use in Reasoning |
|------|----------------|------------------|
| **Cognitive Load** | Fatigue, confusion, delay | Stewardship safety + escalation control |
| **Emotional Intensity** | Anger, anxiety, panic | Tone stabilization + de-escalation filters |
| **Moral Weight** | Harm, injustice, betrayal | Increases moral-computation integrity |
| **Relational Energy** | Cooperation vs. conflict | Adapts interaction model |
| **Adversarial Signatures** | Manipulation, coercion | Activates resilience gating |
| **System Instability** | High variance outputs | Prioritizes stabilization models |

**Outcome**: AI becomes capable of **responding proportionally and insightfully**, not reactively or defensively.

